{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1252/comments/3638078.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:None..None?path=gazebo%2Fgui%2FGuiIface.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1252/_/diff#comment-3638078"}}, "parent": {"id": 3637366, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1252/comments/3637366.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1252/_/diff#comment-3637366"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1252, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1252.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1252"}}, "title": "GuiIface reads GAZEBO_GUI_INI_FILE environment variable"}, "content": {"raw": "Ahh, good point. I forgot about the auto-create functionality. We should keep the auto-create functionality for the HOME case, but not for the `GUI_INI_PATH` case. You can do something like this (note try to avoid using backslash to have text span multiple lines):\n\n\n```\n#!c++\n\nif (guiINIPath)\n{\n  path = guiINIPath;\n  if (!boost::filesystem::exists(path))\n  {\n    gzerr << \"GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH of [\" << path << \"] does not exist. No gui.ini will be loaded.\\n\";\n    result = false;\n    path.clear();\n  }\n}\nelse if (home)\n{\n    // Check the home directory\n    // Construct the path to gui.ini\n    path = home;\n    path = path / \".gazebo\" / \"gui.ini\";\n}\nelse\n{\n    result = false;\n    gzerr << \"Neither HOME nor GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH environment variables were\"\n             << \"found. Unable to locate gui.ini.\" << std::endl;\n}\n\nif (result && !path.empty())\n{\n  gzmsg << \"Reading gui.ini file from \" << path << std::endl;\n  if (!(result = gui::loadINI(path)))\n  {\n    gzerr << \"Unable to read gui.ini from\" << path << std::endl;\n  }\n}\n```\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Ahh, good point. I forgot about the auto-create functionality. We should keep the auto-create functionality for the HOME case, but not for the <code>GUI_INI_PATH</code> case. You can do something like this (note try to avoid using backslash to have text span multiple lines):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-c++\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">guiINIPath</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">guiINIPath</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"n\">boost</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">filesystem</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">exists</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">gzerr</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH of [&quot;</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;] does not exist. No gui.ini will be loaded.</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">false</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clear</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">else</span> <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"c1\">// Check the home directory</span>\n    <span class=\"c1\">// Construct the path to gui.ini</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">home</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;.gazebo&quot;</span> <span class=\"o\">/</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;gui.ini&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">else</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nb\">false</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">gzerr</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;Neither HOME nor GAZEBO_GUI_INI_PATH environment variables were&quot;</span>\n             <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;found. Unable to locate gui.ini.&quot;</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">endl</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">empty</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">gzmsg</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;Reading gui.ini file from &quot;</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">endl</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">gui</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">loadINI</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"p\">)))</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">gzerr</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"s\">&quot;Unable to read gui.ini from&quot;</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span> <span class=\"o\">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"n\">endl</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-10-28T17:52:20.004944+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "inline": {"to": null, "from": null, "outdated": false, "path": "gazebo/gui/GuiIface.cc"}, "updated_on": "2014-10-28T17:52:20.018557+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 3638078}